messages.body: $INPX in my posts below I refer to $ASX as Sensera! This is not the symbol. ASX is the acronym for the Australian Security Exchange and 'SE1' is the symbol for Sensera and is a penny stock. I'd like to thank a certain llama for pointing that out. @stompingllama
$INPX $ASX in addition to my previous post. Just for more info on the covid detecting sensors.

$INPX So I apologize that is isn't the groundbreaking news you were looking for, but I thought some could view this as hope that action is happening behind closed doors, although words are not being spoken outside of those buildings. Or now would be the time to decide to jump ship to a company like $ASX that sounds like they have already a deal made with our government. I am not invested in $ASX (at least for now) so do not have anything to gain if you decide to head that way. But I thought we probably needed news right now of some sort. So we as investors can figure out what we want to do. I implore you to interpret this in your own way and do what you think personally you should do. I however have stated before, technically, and financially I chose Inpixon over about 30 different technology companies and I am going to stay with them. But I wanted to give information and an out for people that want out. Best of luck and may the green find you all!! 💲💲💲

$INPX So this report reads in a way that Nanotron has potential but they could not fufill their goal without the amount of capital it would require. And it would read Inpixon has already made investments on the software side to actually make it a customer solution business to make a profit from it.

SO investors you can take this a good news hearing another CEO speak about Inpixon being ahead and already have made the advancements they just have not been able to get to yet.
Or
Sensera sold Nanotron to Inpixon thinking it didn't have the value it thought.
Or you can think,
I can jump ship on $INPX and jump on $ASX although it is about $4 currently but a COVID-19 detection sensor that has not been formally announced would be big news for a company that works with The US Dept of Defense. The announcement would most likely come by the end of this year for $ASX.

$INPX The company with the already received order is $ASX which is a company that ties to the Department of Defense. I would go into detail but I'm trying to reach a conclusion and a point to this. The next step for $ASX is FDA approval which is said to lead to a HUGE boost in $ASX with a COVID-19 detection device, with an order already in hand and ready to be approved by the FDA. Really big news there and so that boat will sail sometime according to the timetable in this report. Back to Inpixon however. The CEO of Sensera says in the report the following about the sale of Nanotron to Inpixon, "The capital requirements to expand the IOT Solutions business to a systems solutions business were significant and required further time... Inpixon has already made the investments necessary on the system software side to accelerate this business shift to full customer solutions." It then goes on to read it can now focus on the COVID-19 detection sensors. So two things I'll say in the next post.
